import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of S&P 500 index prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['price'])
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of S&P 500 index prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
